Authors:
Adriene Mayra da Silva Soares, Leif Ryvarden, Tatiana
Baptista Gibertoni
Title: A new species of Henningsia from the Brazilian Amazon
Abstract:
Henningsia resupinata is a new species from the brazilian
Amazon. This species is characterized by the white to black, resupinate
basidiomata. The hyphal system is monomitic and the basidiospores are
subglobose to globose.
